result.name: Eat Chinese Restaurant

reviews.text: This very local Chinese restaurant offers various 'yum cha' 'dim sum' at reasonable price and accepted quality. A popular place for the senior citizens around that neighborhood.
Dirty . No one serves you. Foodis quite ok.

A vibrant dim-sum and Cantonese BBQ restaurant crowded by mostly locals. The BBQ goose I had was OK, but the cha-siu and BBQ pork belly was old when served. Dim-sum was OK. Looking at other comments I think quality can vary depending on your luck when you order. Popular with students due to lunch discount.

My first time and last time here. We did not ask for any recommendation for dishes but the head waiter that attended us was enthusiastically telling us about their lobster yee mee. We foolishly ordered it. The lobster was spoilt rotten. Those who ate it had food poisoning the next day. The waiters can't be trusted. Likewise the chefs. They push their expired food to their customers. They have one of the better char siews but their greed for maximum profits at the cost of their customers health will not bring us back here.

dim sum, steamed and/or deep fried, steamed rice in pots, char siu with rice... even fresh seafood,  they have. not the best service,  but a great place to meet with locals, and taxi drivers as well... ;-)
